It was great to be back at my alma mater, Boise State University. My team and I had the chance to tour their state-of-the-art facilities, stand on the iconic blue turf, and meet some of the talented Bronco athletes.

@BoiseState continues to recruit bright students, not only from Idaho, but from across the country.

Wishing the team all the best in Saturday’s game!

The four Lower Snake River dams are critical infrastructure assets of the Pacific Northwest. 

As the furthest inland seaport to the Pacific Ocean, the Lower Snake River system enables international exports and supports a wide array of vital industries: 

✅ Agriculture and grain exporters shipping wheat, barley, soy, and corn;
✅ Barge transportation and logistics operators;
✅ Hydroelectric power generation by the Bonneville Power Administration and regional utilities;
✅ Irrigation and water management for farming;
✅ Recreational and tourism services like river cruises and boat marinas;
✅ Energy-intensive manufacturing such as pulp and paper;
✅ Navigation and supply-chain services critical to our regional economy.

At the same time, robust salmon and steelhead returns prove that healthy fisheries and dam operations can and do coexist successfully.

I am grateful to @POTUS for his actions to protect our region’s infrastructure and marine highway, and I will continue to engage directly with his administration to safeguard our hydropower resources.

In Boise, my team and I met with the leadership at the National Interagency Fire Center (NIFC).

@NIFC_Fire plays a fundamental role in coordinating our nation’s wildfire response and ensuring that federal, state, and tribal wildland personnel have the resources, intelligence, and support needed to prevent and respond to devastating wildfires.

Grateful to their team for the insightful visit and all they do to protect our beautiful Idaho!

My colleagues and I on @NatResources have PASSED our portion of the reconciliation bill. 

We were tasked with identifying $1B in savings and instead achieved $18.5B in new revenue and savings for American taxpayers, all while restoring U.S. energy dominance and wise stewardship of our natural resources and lands.

This legislation will:
✅Reinstate quarterly onshore oil and gas lease sales;
✅Require geothermal lease sales;
✅Resume coal leasing on federal lands;
✅Invest in water infrastructure in the West;
✅Increase timber sales;
✅And mandate long-term timber contracts.
